WEBVTT

00:02.132 --> 00:05.179
[dark music]

00:05.266 --> 00:08.138
♪ ♪

00:26.852 --> 00:28.158
[engine revving]

00:28.289 --> 00:29.768
["Evil Woman" plays]

00:29.899 --> 00:31.857
[man] Oh, yeah.

00:32.032 --> 00:34.425
-[singing along]
-♪ You made a fool of me ♪

00:34.599 --> 00:39.561
♪ But them broken dreams
Have got to end ♪

00:39.648 --> 00:41.737
♪ ♪

00:41.824 --> 00:43.565
-[along with piano]
-♪ Bum bum bum bum ♪

00:43.652 --> 00:45.871
[Gaynor] Oh, my God, Dad,
Dad, will you please

00:45.958 --> 00:48.091
turn off your old person music?

00:48.222 --> 00:50.311
I'm sorry, I can't hear you

00:50.441 --> 00:53.662
over this objectively
perfect song.

00:53.792 --> 00:56.360
An American classic.
Your mom gets it.

00:56.491 --> 00:58.232
-[song continues]
-I can guess what

00:58.362 --> 00:59.711
you're thinking right now.

00:59.842 --> 01:01.104
["Evil Woman" plays]

01:01.235 --> 01:03.628
[woman moaning]

01:03.802 --> 01:07.154
[singer] ♪ 'Cause you ain't
Got no one else to use ♪

01:07.328 --> 01:09.243
-Pat?
-♪ There's an open road ♪

01:09.373 --> 01:10.418
-♪ That leads nowhere ♪
-Honey?

01:10.548 --> 01:12.333
[moaning]

01:12.463 --> 01:14.117
Honey.

01:14.248 --> 01:16.902
-Hmm?
-I was saying, honey,

01:17.033 --> 01:19.427
I'll bet I can guess
what you're thinking.

01:19.514 --> 01:21.472
Probably not.

01:21.603 --> 01:23.692
[dad] Hey, listen, guys,
I wanna tell you something.

01:23.822 --> 01:26.477
This move is really
gonna be great for us.

01:26.564 --> 01:28.392
[Pat] Terry, watch out!

01:28.523 --> 01:31.134
[tires screeching]

01:32.048 --> 01:34.485
-Mom! What the fuck?
-[dog growls]

01:34.616 --> 01:36.835
Gaynor! Do not talk
to your mother like that.

01:36.966 --> 01:38.010
Pat?

01:39.534 --> 01:41.101
What the fuck?

01:41.231 --> 01:43.538
There was a little girl.
She was chasing a ball.

01:43.668 --> 01:46.280
Oh, my God, Terry,
I think you hit her!

01:46.367 --> 01:48.369
What? No! Where?

01:48.499 --> 01:50.284
I-I didn't see anything!
I saw nothing!

01:50.371 --> 01:52.329
[game sounds]

01:52.460 --> 01:55.463
Wait.
Dad killed a little girl?

01:55.593 --> 01:57.421
[door open beeping]

01:57.552 --> 02:00.511
[dark music]

02:00.598 --> 02:03.427
♪ ♪

02:07.170 --> 02:09.825
[exhaling] Oh, God. Ha.

02:09.955 --> 02:12.306
Musta been a deer.

02:12.436 --> 02:14.351
You know, w-we didn't have
any deer back in Brooklyn.

02:14.438 --> 02:16.136
They're all over the place
here in Connecticut.

02:16.266 --> 02:17.963
-I'm sure that's what it is.
-It wasn't a deer!

02:18.094 --> 02:19.791
It wasn't a deer!
She was--she was wearing a--

02:19.922 --> 02:23.273
a flowered dress, and she had
ribbons in her hair.

02:23.404 --> 02:25.275
Well, I can actually
see how an antler

02:25.362 --> 02:27.234
could look like a ribbon--

02:27.364 --> 02:28.539
I know what a fucking deer
looks like, Terry!

02:28.670 --> 02:30.976
Just keep looking!

02:31.107 --> 02:33.153
-For what?
-Oh, God.

02:33.283 --> 02:35.546
What-what are we looking for?
Th-there's nothing here. Hello!

02:36.547 --> 02:37.983
I mean, come on.

02:38.114 --> 02:40.464
-[game sounds continue]
-[dog whines]

02:43.424 --> 02:44.990
-[Terry sighs]
-Did we kill someone?

02:45.121 --> 02:46.818
Ha. No.

02:46.949 --> 02:48.951
No, it was a false alarm.

02:50.561 --> 02:51.693
Okay?

02:53.782 --> 02:55.827
-[engine turns]
-But like I was saying, guys.

02:55.958 --> 02:57.612
[dog grumbling]

02:57.742 --> 03:00.354
This move really is
gonna be great for us.

03:00.441 --> 03:03.183
[moody music]

03:03.313 --> 03:06.142
[woman vocalizing eerily]

03:06.316 --> 03:09.493
♪ ♪

03:09.798 --> 03:11.843
[dramatic musical sting]

03:11.974 --> 03:14.890
[Terry] Welcome to
Casa de Phelps.

03:15.020 --> 03:17.675
Just slightly bigger than our
apartment in Brooklyn.

03:17.806 --> 03:19.721
Are you shitting us?

03:19.851 --> 03:23.028
[Terry] No, Gaynor,
we're not shitting you.

03:23.159 --> 03:26.336
When your mom and I saw it,
we fell in love with it.

03:26.467 --> 03:28.208
And you will too.

03:28.338 --> 03:29.818
[game sounds stop]

03:29.948 --> 03:31.428
Wait.

03:31.559 --> 03:33.561
Why are we moving to a hotel?

03:33.691 --> 03:35.824
-[car door opens]
-It's not a hotel.

03:35.911 --> 03:37.956
This is our new house.

03:38.087 --> 03:40.524
It's a hundred miles away
from all the crazy in the city.

03:40.655 --> 03:42.483
In other words,
Mom boned some rando,

03:42.613 --> 03:44.398
-so we had to move here.
-Hey--no!

03:44.485 --> 03:47.270
It's not about that.
It's a great house.

03:47.357 --> 03:49.229
And I got it 200 below asking,

03:49.359 --> 03:51.318
in this market!

03:51.405 --> 03:53.885
Gaynor, your bedroom is on
the opposite side of the house

03:54.016 --> 03:55.844
from ours, and Jake,
you have your own bathroom

03:55.931 --> 03:57.324
with a lock on the door.

03:57.411 --> 03:59.935
-[Jake] Sweet.
-Just say that then.

04:03.199 --> 04:04.896
-You okay?
-Yeah.

04:05.027 --> 04:06.420
Yeah, it was just...

04:06.550 --> 04:08.117
-long drive.
-Yeah.

04:08.248 --> 04:09.901
Should we check it out?

04:13.557 --> 04:16.430
-Hey, you need some help?
-No, I got it.

04:16.517 --> 04:18.040
[moody music]

04:18.170 --> 04:19.737
Hi.

04:21.043 --> 04:23.741
-We're um, we're just moving in.
-[Terry] Pat, little help.

04:23.872 --> 04:26.962
Honey, I'm talking to someone.

04:30.618 --> 04:33.011
[grunts]
Fuck me.

04:33.664 --> 04:35.840
[tour guide] She is the pearl
of Shining Vale.

04:35.971 --> 04:38.539
Of course, you remember
her grand staircase

04:38.669 --> 04:40.410
leads us down to the foyer.

04:40.541 --> 04:42.804
Living room, dining room,
family room.

04:42.891 --> 04:45.894
No basement, but the attic
has plenty of storage.

04:45.981 --> 04:48.418
[Pat] I'm gonna be using
the attic as my writing annex.

04:48.549 --> 04:50.202
Oh, you're a writer!

04:50.333 --> 04:51.856
Anything I might have read
or seen?

04:51.987 --> 04:53.380
Do you ever read
"Cressida: Unbound"?

04:53.510 --> 04:55.599
That was Pat's first novel.

04:55.730 --> 04:58.385
Oh! The lady porn.

04:59.211 --> 05:01.692
Huh. What was that...
20 years ago?

05:01.823 --> 05:04.260
No, it was 17,
and it's not porn.

05:04.391 --> 05:05.914
It's a women's
empowerment story

05:06.001 --> 05:08.090
about a sex addict
that makes bad choices.

05:08.220 --> 05:09.526
Just a complete
work of fiction.

05:09.657 --> 05:11.093
-Mm.
-It is fiction.

05:11.223 --> 05:12.137
That's what I'm saying.
It's amazing work.

05:12.268 --> 05:14.270
It's fiction.

05:15.445 --> 05:17.447
[Pat] I'm hoping that being
out in the country

05:17.578 --> 05:19.536
is gonna help me find
my muse again.

05:19.667 --> 05:22.757
Oh. These old ladies have
plenty of stories to tell.

05:23.497 --> 05:25.760
[Terry] They're just gonna
leave this piano, huh?

05:25.890 --> 05:28.066
Used to tickle the ivories
at college.

05:28.153 --> 05:29.981
-I went to Penn.
-Mm.

05:30.112 --> 05:31.548
So, uh...

05:31.679 --> 05:34.812
[keys thwanging, clanking]

05:34.943 --> 05:36.858
Oh. It's dead.

05:36.988 --> 05:39.469
Yeah, I have a question.
It's--it's really cold in here.

05:39.600 --> 05:40.949
Does the heat work?

05:41.079 --> 05:42.994
Uh, should be.
Yeah, just give it a bit.

05:43.125 --> 05:45.127
I mean, the house has been
empty for nearly two years.

05:46.084 --> 05:48.130
[quietly] She's probably
not used to having people

05:48.260 --> 05:49.610
inside of her.

05:50.915 --> 05:52.221
Anyway...ha.

05:52.352 --> 05:55.093
Welcome to Shining Vale.
Here you go!

05:55.224 --> 05:56.791
Thank you.

05:56.921 --> 05:58.749
Bye.

05:58.880 --> 06:00.969
[door opens, closes]

06:01.099 --> 06:02.927
That was a really fucking
weird way to put that,

06:03.058 --> 06:05.365
-wasn't it?
-No!

06:09.499 --> 06:11.283
[Terry] And here we go.

06:11.414 --> 06:13.851
I found a hatchet
out in the shed.

06:13.982 --> 06:16.245
Or maybe it was an axe.
[panting]

06:16.376 --> 06:18.769
Hatchet, axe--I- I don't know!

06:19.509 --> 06:21.381
All I know is I went to town
on some wood,

06:21.511 --> 06:23.948
and honestly,
I feel like a different man.

06:24.079 --> 06:26.386
I don't know why
I'm just so cold.

06:26.473 --> 06:27.822
Maybe it's menopause.

06:27.952 --> 06:29.345
Mm.

06:29.476 --> 06:31.782
Menopause makes you hot,
wise-ass.

06:31.913 --> 06:33.393
[Pat] No phones at the table.

06:33.523 --> 06:35.307
We don't have a table, so...

06:35.438 --> 06:37.005
No, no, no, Mom's right,
Gaynor.

06:37.092 --> 06:39.573
Come on, phones down.
Everybody--you too, mister.

06:39.703 --> 06:41.575
-[Pat] Come on.
-[Terry] Let's go.

06:41.705 --> 06:43.054
[Terry] This is family time.

06:43.141 --> 06:45.056
Hey, you know what I wish?

06:45.187 --> 06:46.580
That Brooklyn's
Second Best Movers didn't lose

06:46.667 --> 06:49.278
-our dining room table?
-No...

06:49.409 --> 06:50.758
That Roxy didn't just
take a shit in the living room?

06:50.888 --> 06:52.716
[Pat] Damn it.
I just walked her!

06:52.803 --> 06:54.109
No. You can clean up
the poop later.

06:54.239 --> 06:55.676
Just--this is family time.

06:55.806 --> 06:57.765
I wish we had done this
a long time ago.

06:57.895 --> 06:59.331
But I wanna know
what everybody's

06:59.419 --> 07:01.377
looking most forward to
in the new house.

07:01.508 --> 07:03.248
I will start.

07:03.379 --> 07:06.077
When I was out there
in the shed chopping wood,

07:06.208 --> 07:09.646
I saw what I think
is beaver scat.

07:09.733 --> 07:11.431
-[Pat] Oh. [laughs]
-I think we're near a creek.

07:11.561 --> 07:14.521
Jake, what do you say
you and I go exploring?

07:14.651 --> 07:16.914
Outside?

07:17.045 --> 07:19.047
Yes, outside.

07:19.177 --> 07:20.527
[quietly] Okay.

07:20.657 --> 07:22.529
Okay! Okay.
Let's build on that.

07:22.616 --> 07:24.226
Gaynor, what're you looking
most forward to?

07:24.356 --> 07:25.619
Emancipation.

07:25.749 --> 07:27.185
Kay. You lose your turn.
Pat?

07:27.316 --> 07:29.579
Well, um,
I'm looking forward to

07:29.710 --> 07:32.060
finishing my book, obviously,
but, um,

07:32.190 --> 07:35.367
mostly...
reconnecting with my family.

07:35.498 --> 07:37.326
[Terry] Hear, hear.
Family.

07:37.413 --> 07:39.459
-Cheers all around.
-[Pat] Cheers.

07:40.547 --> 07:42.984
[Terry] Okay.

07:43.071 --> 07:45.639
-Can we be excused?
-Yeah, I think that's fine.

07:50.687 --> 07:52.907
We're gonna do this
every night!

07:53.037 --> 07:54.212
[running footsteps upstairs]

07:54.343 --> 07:56.911
[both chuckling]

07:56.998 --> 07:58.129
[doors thud closed]

07:58.260 --> 07:59.740
Let's make love.

07:59.870 --> 08:01.655
Really?

08:01.785 --> 08:04.092
Well, we haven't had any action
since you f--

08:04.222 --> 08:06.268
[small laugh]

08:06.355 --> 08:07.704
Fuh--fra--

08:07.835 --> 08:09.097
I can't say it.

08:09.227 --> 08:11.012
[laughing softly]

08:11.142 --> 08:12.274
[dramatic musical sting]

08:12.361 --> 08:15.233
[Pat] I didn't plan it.

08:15.320 --> 08:17.758
Frank came over to fix the--
the faucet.

08:17.845 --> 08:19.803
He took off his shirt,

08:19.934 --> 08:22.110
and the-and the next thing you
know, i-it just happened.

08:22.240 --> 08:23.981
Mm. You know anybody
takes their shirt off

08:24.068 --> 08:26.288
-to fix a faucet?
-Oh, I'm so sorry, Terry.

08:26.418 --> 08:28.116
He didn't even fix
the goddamn faucet.

08:28.246 --> 08:31.336
I t--I've been in a really
dark place lately.

08:31.423 --> 08:34.165
I-I don't--I don't e--I didn't
feel like it was even me.

08:34.296 --> 08:36.298
[therapist] Has anything
changed recently?

08:36.385 --> 08:37.995
No. Nothing!

08:38.126 --> 08:39.736
I-I'm-I'm...

08:39.867 --> 08:42.217
my kids are teenagers,
so they ignore me.

08:42.347 --> 08:44.349
Terry's at work,
a-and I'm home alone

08:44.480 --> 08:46.787
in our tiny, tiny apartment

08:46.874 --> 08:48.353
just trying to write my book.

08:48.484 --> 08:50.268
And every single day...

08:50.355 --> 08:52.183
is exactly the same.

08:52.314 --> 08:54.055
-[Pat sniffling]
-And what is so wrong

08:54.142 --> 08:54.969
-with that?
-[Pat sighs]

08:58.276 --> 08:59.887
I'm just really fucking sad.

09:02.280 --> 09:03.804
[therapist] Is there
depression in your family?

09:03.934 --> 09:05.632
-Her mother's psychotic.
-[Pat] My God.

09:05.762 --> 09:07.895
Why would you bring
my mom into this?

09:08.025 --> 09:10.288
He asked about depression,
not psychosis.

09:10.375 --> 09:13.074
[therapist] No, i-is your mom
depressed?

09:13.204 --> 09:15.337
Yes, she happens to be, but...

09:15.467 --> 09:17.557
-and psychotic.
-[therapist] Hmm.

09:17.687 --> 09:19.341
Have you been on drugs
before or--

09:19.471 --> 09:20.777
[Terry] She was a complete
alcoholic.

09:20.908 --> 09:22.431
-That count?
-[therapist] Mm.

09:22.562 --> 09:25.303
I've been sober
for over 16 years.

09:25.434 --> 09:27.131
[therapist] Right. I meant
antidepressants, which,

09:27.262 --> 09:29.656
given your history
and symptoms,

09:29.786 --> 09:31.396
uh...I think
we should start there.

09:31.527 --> 09:33.877
[Pat] Oh. What are
the side effects?

09:34.008 --> 09:36.271
Short-term--insomnia,

09:36.401 --> 09:40.362
weight gain, extreme drop
in sexual desire.

09:42.059 --> 09:44.453
-[Terry] Yeah, looks good.
-I could live with that.

09:45.933 --> 09:47.151
[belt clatters]

09:47.238 --> 09:48.631
[whispers] Pat...

09:48.718 --> 09:50.851
come on!

09:50.981 --> 09:52.548
Come on.

09:56.726 --> 09:58.423
Wild man. Ha.

09:58.510 --> 10:00.687
[Terry] Patty...

10:00.817 --> 10:02.863
[Pat laughs]

10:02.993 --> 10:05.779
[Terry grunting]

10:05.909 --> 10:07.781
It's hooked on my watch, okay?

10:07.911 --> 10:09.870
God damn it.

10:10.000 --> 10:12.350
I'm hooked on the--
[hoarsely] my watch.

10:12.481 --> 10:14.265
-I'm stuck. Just--
-Let me help.

10:14.396 --> 10:16.093
[Terry] Reach- reach up
and grab that right here.

10:16.224 --> 10:17.486
[Pat] Okay.
Oh, you really are stuck.

10:17.617 --> 10:18.922
-[Terry] Yeah--
-You know what?

10:19.053 --> 10:20.358
Let's just put it back on.
Yeah.

10:20.489 --> 10:21.969
-Here.
[Terry] Okay, okay. Okay...

10:22.099 --> 10:23.579
[Pat] There.

10:23.710 --> 10:25.973
Listen, why don't you
go upstairs...

10:26.103 --> 10:27.496
-Yeah?
-And I'll be there

10:27.583 --> 10:29.803
-right after I straighten up.
-Yeah.

10:29.933 --> 10:31.848
And then you and me...

10:31.979 --> 10:33.633
are gonna consecrate
our new house.

10:33.763 --> 10:35.112
[Pat] Okay!

10:35.243 --> 10:36.548
Can't wait.

10:37.985 --> 10:39.639
Whoo! Love this place!

10:49.910 --> 10:51.781
[piano note playing]

10:52.695 --> 10:54.044
Terry?

10:56.220 --> 10:59.659
[jazzy music plays]

10:59.833 --> 11:02.705
♪ ♪

11:02.836 --> 11:05.665
[eerie off-key music]

11:05.839 --> 11:07.231
♪ ♪

11:07.362 --> 11:08.972
Hello?

11:09.103 --> 11:11.845
[suspenseful music]

11:12.019 --> 11:14.935
♪ ♪

11:15.065 --> 11:17.241
[shivers]

11:17.328 --> 11:19.243
[light rattling]

11:19.374 --> 11:20.462
Oh.

11:29.819 --> 11:32.561
[tense music escalates]

11:32.735 --> 11:34.955
♪ ♪

11:36.521 --> 11:38.610
[insects chirping]

11:46.706 --> 11:48.316
[hinges squeaking]

11:49.491 --> 11:51.536
[Roxy barks]

11:51.667 --> 11:53.147
-[growling]
-What?

11:53.277 --> 11:55.540
-[snarling]
-Do you have to go potty?

11:55.671 --> 11:58.195
Roxy, do not shit
in this house again.

11:58.326 --> 12:00.284
[three taps]

12:09.163 --> 12:10.555
Aah!

12:10.686 --> 12:13.515
[eerie music]

12:13.645 --> 12:15.909
[jazz playing]

12:16.039 --> 12:17.345
Terry, I saw someone
downstairs.

12:17.475 --> 12:19.608
Huh? Where?

12:19.739 --> 12:21.741
-You saw someone in the house?
-No. She was in the backyard.

12:21.871 --> 12:23.394
I was in the living room.
[panting]

12:23.481 --> 12:25.222
Okay, but the living room...

12:25.353 --> 12:26.963
the living room doesn't
overlook the backyard.

12:27.050 --> 12:28.486
Okay, whatever that room is

12:28.617 --> 12:30.793
that--that does overlook
the backyard!

12:30.924 --> 12:32.752
You're talking about
the family room.

12:32.882 --> 12:34.492
[Pat] Okay, fine!
I-I was in the family room

12:34.579 --> 12:35.972
and she was outside
looking in the window!

12:36.059 --> 12:37.234
-What'd she look like?
-I don't know!

12:37.365 --> 12:39.149
She was-she was like...
old-fashioned.

12:39.280 --> 12:40.890
Like your mother.

12:41.021 --> 12:42.370
My mother isn't old-fashioned
looking, Pat.

12:42.500 --> 12:43.850
If anything, she's handsome.

12:43.980 --> 12:46.548
Wha...Jesus, fuck, Terry!
Okay!

12:46.678 --> 12:48.376
-There's a handsome-looking...
-Okay...

12:48.506 --> 12:50.030
-Woman, notyour mother...
-Shh!

12:50.160 --> 12:51.945
Hovering outside
the family room window.

12:52.075 --> 12:52.989
-[Pat] Okay.
-Oh, my God!

12:53.076 --> 12:54.512
[thud]

12:54.599 --> 12:55.905
Are you talking about
the library?

12:55.992 --> 12:57.777
Just fucking go downstairs!

13:01.041 --> 13:02.999
[door hinges creak]

13:03.086 --> 13:04.435
[Pat] Nothin' out there.

13:04.566 --> 13:06.786
-Are you sure?
-I didn't see anything.

13:06.873 --> 13:08.483
I mean, nothing unusual.

13:08.570 --> 13:10.137
Must've been a deer.

13:10.224 --> 13:11.965
The window is ten feet
off the ground.

13:12.095 --> 13:13.575
How could it be a deer?

13:13.705 --> 13:15.142
Well, how could it be
a handsome woman?

13:15.272 --> 13:17.231
I didn't say handsome.
I said old-fashioned.

13:17.318 --> 13:18.710
And I don't know why you think

13:18.798 --> 13:20.495
I don't know what a deer
looks like.

13:20.625 --> 13:22.802
Okay, well, whatever it was,
it's outside, okay?

13:22.932 --> 13:25.587
Tomorrow I'll hire somebody
to put up floodlights.

13:25.674 --> 13:27.458
-Thank you.
-We had a very good handyman,

13:27.545 --> 13:29.634
-but obviously--okay.
-I know, I got it.

